<p>JavaScript powers 98% of modern websites. Yet most developers ship JavaScript-heavy apps without checking if Google can actually read the content.</p>
<p>That blind spot costs real rankings. Pages that render only on the client side take up to 9 times longer for Google to process than static HTML. And 25% of JavaScript content on popular sites never gets indexed at all.</p>
<p>This guide covers everything you need to know about javascript SEO in one place. We publish 3,500+ blog posts across 70+ industries, and JavaScript rendering issues are one of the most common <a href="/glossary/technical-seo/">technical SEO</a> problems we see.</p>
